                                <p>
                                    <locus from="Note_1r" to="Note_1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In black ink by a modern hand: notes on the contents and proper title of the volume.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="Note_1v" to="Note_1v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Notes in black ink by a modern hand: <quote>Tidebok på Latin och Danska skrifven af Johanna Nilsdotter torde vara bästa titeln</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="Note_2r" to="Note_2r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In dark brown ink by a modern hand: <quote>Johanne Nielsdatters (jfr. Bl. 78.v.) Tidebog (jf. Christiern Pedersens danska Skrifter utg. af CJBrandt, BTh. Fenger II s. 497.)</quote>
                                    </note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page in brown ink by a modern hand: <quote>Ottho Kragh</quote>. Below in black ink: <quote>33</quote>. Middle of page in black ink in a modern hand: <quote>Cursus Beatae Mariae (Vor Frue Psaltare). Dansk hdskr. fr. slutet af 1400-talet. början af 1500. Innehåller latinska texter till Danska "Vor frue tijder", jemte åtskilliga böner.</quote>
                                    </note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1v" to="1v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In brown ink in a later medieval hand (cursive): <quote xml:lang="la">Psal. lxvi: Deus misereatur nostri</quote> (in total 12 lines).</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="4r" to="4r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In black ink by a medieval hand, for 8 February: <quote>Helena drongne</quote>, for 9 February: <quote>Appolonia</quote>
                                    </note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="4v" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top left margin, in black ink by a modern hand: question-mark. Top of page, to the right, in brown ink in a medieval hand: <quote xml:lang="la">obitus sanctis walburgis virginis</quote>. Left margin, in pencil: Roman numerals continuing over <locus from="5r" to="6r" scheme="folios"/>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="6v" to="6v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Left margin, in black ink by a modern hand: two question-marks. In brown ink by a medieval hand: <quote>Obiit dominus Iohannes Episcopus Arusiensis Anno Domini mdlxxxii</quote>, possibly referring to <persName>Jens Pederssøn Skielderup</persName>, bishop of<placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100312"> Bergen</placeName>, d. <date when="1582"/>. <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107247">Nielsen (1956)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="224" to="224" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl> suggests Jens Iversen Lange, bishop of Aarhus, d. <date when="1482"/>; <quote>halnardi martiris</quote> referring to St Hallvard, May 15.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="8v" to="8v" scheme="folios"/>
